      function appendMqttLog(topic, message, type = 'received') {

      if (type === 'sent') {
      messageClass += ' mqtt-log-sent'; // Dodaj klasę dla wysłanych wiadomości (możesz dodać styl w CSS)
      } else if (type === 'error') {
      messageClass += ' mqtt-log-error'; // Dodaj klasę dla błędów
      }
      logEntry.innerHTML = `<span class="mqtt-log-time">[${time}]</span> <span class="mqtt-log-topic">${topic}</span>: <span class="${messageClass}">${message}</span>`;
      mqttLogDiv.prepend(logEntry);
      while (mqttLogDiv.children.length > 50) {
      mqttLogDiv.removeChild(mqttLogDiv.lastChild);
      }
      }

      function connectMQTT() {
      if (client && client.connected) {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", "Już połączono z brokerem.");
      return;
      }
      const broker = mqttBrokerInput.value;
      const port = mqttPortInput.value;
      const username = mqttUsernameInput.value;
      const password = mqttPasswordInput.value;
      // Użycie protokołu WebSocket (wss://) dla połączeń z przeglądarki hostowanej na GitHubie
      // Port 8084 jest typowy dla WSS w brokerze EMQX.
      const mqttUrl = `wss://${broker}:${port}/mqtt`;
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", `Próba połączenia z brokerem: ${mqttUrl}`);
      client = mqtt.connect(mqttUrl, {
      clientId: 'web_client_' + Math.random().toString(16).substr(2, 8),
      username: username,
      password: password,
      clean: true,
      keepalive: 60
      });
      client.on('connect', () => {
      updateMqttStatus(true);
      // Subskrybuj tematy, na których ESP32 publikuje stan
      client.subscribe(MQTT_TOPICS.state, (err) => {
      if (!err) {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", `Subskrybowano: ${MQTT_TOPICS.state}`);
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT ERROR", `Błąd subskrypcji ${MQTT_TOPICS.state}: ${err.message}`, 'error');
      }
      });
      client.subscribe(MQTT_TOPICS.power, (err) => { // Subskrybuj temat power
      if (!err) {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", `Subskrybowano: ${MQTT_TOPICS.power}`);
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT ERROR", `Błąd subskrypcji ${MQTT_TOPICS.power}: ${err.message}`, 'error');
      }
      });
      client.subscribe(MQTT_TOPICS.targetTemp, (err) => { // Subskrybuj temat target_temp
      if (!err) {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", `Subskrybowano: ${MQTT_TOPICS.targetTemp}`);
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT ERROR", `Błąd subskrypcji ${MQTT_TOPICS.targetTemp}: ${err.message}`, 'error');
      }
      });
      client.subscribe(MQTT_TOPICS.control, (err) => { // Subskrybuj temat control
      if (!err) {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT", `Subskrybowano: ${MQTT_TOPICS.control}`);
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("MQTT ERROR", `Błąd subskrypcji ${MQTT_TOPICS.control}: ${err.message}`, 'error');
      }
      });
      });
      client.on('message', (topic, message) => {
      const msgString = message.toString();
      appendMqttLog(topic, msgString);
      // Obsługa tematu state (oczekuje JSON)
      if (topic === MQTT_TOPICS.state) {
      try {
      const data = JSON.parse(msgString);
      console.log("Parsed MQTT state data:", data); // Loguj sparsowane dane
      // Weryfikacja, czy dane zawierają podstawowe, oczekiwane pola
      if (data && typeof data.power === 'string' && typeof data.water_temp === 'number') {
      if (data.timestamp_ms === undefined) {
      data.timestamp_ms = Date.now();
      }
      updateUI(data);
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("STAN DANYCH NIEPRAWIDŁOWY", `Odebrano niekompletne/nieprawidłowe dane stanu na ${topic}. Wiadomość: "${msgString}"`, 'error');
      console.warn("Received incomplete/invalid state data:", data);
      }
      } catch (e) {
      appendMqttLog("BŁĄD PARSOWANIA JSON", `Nie udało się sparsować wiadomości na ${topic}: ${e.message}. Wiadomość: "${msgString}"`, 'error');
      console.error(`MQTT: Failed to parse MQTT message on ${topic}:`, e, "Message:", msgString);
      }
      }
      // Obsługa tematu power (oczekuje prostego tekstu ON/OFF)
      else if (topic === MQTT_TOPICS.power) {
      console.log(`Odebrano komendę POWER na ${topic}: ${msgString}`);
      if (msgString === "ON" || msgString === "OFF") {
      if (powerBtn) {
      if (msgString === "ON") {
      powerBtn.innerHTML = '<i class="fas fa-power-off"></i> WŁĄCZONY';
      powerBtn.classList.remove('power-off');
      powerBtn.classList.add('success');
      } else {
      powerBtn.innerHTML = '<i class="fas fa-power-off"></i> WYŁĄCZONY';
      powerBtn.classList.remove('success');
      powerBtn.classList.add('power-off');
      }
      }
      } else {
      console.warn(`Odebrano nieznaną komendę POWER: ${msgString}`);
      }
      }
      // Obsługa tematu target_temp (oczekuje prostej liczby jako tekst)
      else if (topic === MQTT_TOPICS.targetTemp) {
      console.log(`Odebrano temperaturę docelową na ${topic}: ${msgString}`);
      const receivedTemp = parseFloat(msgString);
      if (!isNaN(receivedTemp)) {
      if (targetSlider) targetSlider.value = receivedTemp.toFixed(0);
      if (targetDisplay) targetDisplay.textContent = receivedTemp.toFixed(0) + '°C';
      if (targetTemp) targetTemp.textContent = receivedTemp.toFixed(0);
      } else {
      console.warn(`Odebrano nieprawidłową temperaturę docelową: ${msgString}`);
      }
      }
      // Obsługa tematu control (oczekuje JSON) - dla komend z innych źródeł
      else if (topic === MQTT_TOPICS.control) {
      try {
      const data = JSON.parse(msgString);
      console.log("Parsed MQTT control data:", data);
      // Możesz tutaj dodać logikę reagowania na komendy sterujące z innych źródeł
      } catch (e) {
      appendMqttLog("BŁĄD PARSOWANIA JSON", `Nie udało się sparsować wiadomości na ${topic}: ${e.message}. Wiadomość: "${msgString}"`, 'error');
      console.error(`MQTT: Failed to parse MQTT control message on ${topic}:`, e, "Message:", msgString);
      }
      }
      });
      client.on('error', (err) => {
      appendMqttLog("BŁĄD POŁĄCZENIA MQTT", `Wystąpił błąd: ${err.message}`, 'error');
      console.error('MQTT: An error occurred:', err);
      updateMqttStatus(false);
      if (client) {
      client.end();
      client = null;
      }
      });
      client.on('close', () => {
      updateMqttStatus(false);
      appendMqttLog("POŁĄCZENIE ZAMKNIĘTE", "Połączenie MQTT zostało zamknięte.");
      client = null;
      });
      client.on('offline', () => {
      appendMqttLog("KLIENT OFFLINE", "Klient MQTT jest offline.");
      updateMqttStatus(false);
      });
      client.on('reconnect', () => {
      appendMqttLog("PONOWNE ŁĄCZENIE", "Próba ponownego połączenia z brokerem MQTT...");

      if (mqttStatusIndicator) {
      mqttStatusIndicator.classList.remove('connected');
      mqttStatusIndicator.classList.add('disconnected');
      }
      });
      }
      function disconnectMQTT() {

      function publishMqttMessage(topic, message) {

      console.warn("MQTT client not connected. Message not sent.");
      }
      }
      // Helper function to format seconds into HH:MM:SS
      function formatTime(totalSeconds) {
      if (typeof totalSeconds !== 'number' || isNaN(totalSeconds)) return 'N/A';
      const hours = Math.floor(totalSeconds / 3600);
      const minutes = Math.floor((totalSeconds % 3600) / 60);
      const seconds = totalSeconds % 60;
      return `${hours.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:${minutes.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:${seconds.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
      }
      // Function to calculate average pellet consumption for a given duration
      function calculateAverageConsumption(durationMinutes = 60) {
      if (!chartData.pellet_consumption || chartData.pellet_consumption.length === 0) {
      return 0.0;
      }
      const now = luxon.DateTime.now();
      const cutoffTime = now.minus({ minutes: durationMinutes }).toMillis();
      const recentData = chartData.pellet_consumption.filter(point => point.x >= cutoffTime);
      if (recentData.length === 0) {
      return 0.0;
      }
      const totalConsumptionRate = recentData.reduce((sum, point) => sum + point.y, 0);
      return totalConsumptionRate / recentData.length;
      }
      // Functions to aggregate data for bar charts
      function aggregateDailyConsumption(history) {
      const dailyData = new Map();
      const now = luxon.DateTime.now();
      if (!history) return { labels: [], data: [] }; // Zabezpieczenie przed undefined
      history.forEach(point => {
      const dateTime = luxon.DateTime.fromMillis(point.x);
      const dateKey = dateTime.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd');
      const consumptionKg = (typeof point.y === 'number' && !isNaN(point.y)) ? point.y / 60 : 0;
      if (dailyData.has(dateKey)) {
      dailyData.set(dateKey, dailyData.get(dateKey) + consumptionKg);
      } else {
      dailyData.set(dateKey, consumptionKg);
      }
      });
      const labels = [];
      const data = [];
      for (let i = 6; i >= 0; i--) {
      const date = now.minus({ days: i });
      const dateKey = date.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd');
      labels.push(date.toFormat('EEE dd.MM'));
      data.push(dailyData.has(dateKey) ? dailyData.get(dateKey) : 0);
      }
      return { labels, data };
      }
      function aggregateMonthlyConsumption(history) {
      const monthlyData = new Map();
      const now = luxon.DateTime.now();
      if (!history) return { labels: [], data: [] }; // Zabezpieczenie przed undefined
      history.forEach(point => {
      const dateTime = luxon.DateTime.fromMillis(point.x);
      const dateKey = dateTime.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd');
      const consumptionKg = (typeof point.y === 'number' && !isNaN(point.y)) ? point.y / 60 : 0;
      if (monthlyData.has(dateKey)) {
      monthlyData.set(dateKey, monthlyData.get(dateKey) + consumptionKg);
      } else {
      monthlyData.set(dateKey, consumptionKg);
      }
      });
      const labels = [];
      const data = [];
      for (let i = 29; i >= 0; i--) {
      const date = now.minus({ days: i });
      const dateKey = date.toFormat('dd.MM');
      labels.push(dateKey);
      data.push(monthlyData.has(dateKey) ? monthlyData.get(dateKey) : 0);
      }
      return { labels, data };
      }
      function aggregateYearlyConsumption(history) {
      const yearlyData = new Map();
      const now = luxon.DateTime.now();
      if (!history) return { labels: [], data: [] }; // Zabezpieczenie przed undefined
      history.forEach(point => {
      const dateTime = luxon.DateTime.fromMillis(point.x);
      const monthKey = dateTime.toFormat('yyyy-MM');
      const consumptionKg = (typeof point.y === 'number' && !isNaN(point.y)) ? point.y / 60 : 0;
      if (yearlyData.has(monthKey)) {
      yearlyData.set(monthKey, yearlyData.get(monthKey) + consumptionKg);
      } else {
      yearlyData.set(monthKey, consumptionKg);
      }
      });
      const labels = [];
      const data = [];
      for (let i = 11; i >= 0; i--) {
      const month = now.minus({ months: i }).startOf('month');
      const monthKey = month.toFormat('yyyy-MM');
      labels.push(month.toFormat('MMM yyyy'));
      data.push(yearlyData.has(monthKey) ? yearlyData.get(monthKey) : 0);
      }
      return { labels, data };
      }
      function aggregateGlobalConsumption(history) {
      const globalData = new Map();
      if (!history) return { labels: [], data: [] }; // Zabezpieczenie przed undefined
      history.forEach(point => {
      const dateTime = luxon.DateTime.fromMillis(point.x);
      const yearKey = dateTime.toFormat('yyyy');
      const consumptionKg = (typeof point.y === 'number' && !isNaN(point.y)) ? point.y / 60 : 0;
      if (globalData.has(yearKey)) {
      globalData.set(yearKey, globalData.get(yearKey) + consumptionKg);
      } else {
      globalData.set(yearKey, consumptionKg);
      }
      });
      const sortedYears = Array.from(globalData.keys()).sort();
      const labels = sortedYears;
      const data = sortedYears.map(year => globalData.get(year));
      return { labels, data };
      }

      // Add a single new data point to the chart
      function addChartDataPoint(data) {
      const timestamp = data.timestamp_ms;
      // Temperature Chart Data
      chartData.water_temp.push({ x: timestamp, y: data.water_temp });
      chartData.room_temp.push({ x: timestamp, y: data.room_temp });
      chartData.burner_temp.push({ x: timestamp, y: data.burner_temp });
      chartData.exhaust_temp.push({ x: timestamp, y: data.exhaust_temp });
      // Limit history data points for temperature chart
      while (chartData.water_temp.length > 200) { // Keep last 200 points (approx 200 minutes)
      chartData.water_temp.shift();
      chartData.room_temp.shift();
      chartData.burner_temp.shift();
      chartData.exhaust_temp.shift();
      }
      if (temperatureChartInstance) { // Dodano sprawdzenie instancji wykresu
      temperatureChartInstance.data.labels = chartData.water_temp.map(point => point.x);
      temperatureChartInstance.data.datasets[chartDatasetMap['water_temp']].data = chartData.water_temp;
      temperatureChartInstance.data.datasets[chartDatasetMap['room_temp']].data = chartData.room_temp;
      temperatureChartInstance.data.datasets[chartDatasetMap['burner_temp']].data = chartData.burner_temp;
      temperatureChartInstance.data.datasets[chartDatasetMap['exhaust_temp']].data = chartData.exhaust_temp;
      temperatureChartInstance.update();
      }
      // Consumption Chart Data
      chartData.pellet_consumption.push({ x: timestamp, y: data.currentPelletConsumptionRate });
      // Limit history data points for consumption chart
      while (chartData.pellet_consumption.length > 200) { // Keep last 200 points
      chartData.pellet_consumption.shift();
      }
      if (consumptionChartInstance) { // Dodano sprawdzenie instancji wykresu
      consumptionChartInstance.data.labels = chartData.pellet_consumption.map(point => point.x);
      consumptionChartInstance.data.datasets[0].data = chartData.pellet_consumption;
      consumptionChartInstance.update();
      }
      }
      // Update UI based on state
      function updateUI(data) {
      console.log("updateUI called with data:", data); // Loguj cały obiekt data
      // Zabezpiecz przed undefined/null przed wywołaniem toFixed()
      if (waterTempDisplay && typeof data.water_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.water_temp)) waterTempDisplay.textContent = data.water_temp.toFixed(1) + '°C';
      else if (waterTempDisplay) waterTempDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      if (roomTempDisplay && typeof data.room_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.room_temp)) roomTempDisplay.textContent = data.room_temp.toFixed(1) + '°C';
      else if (roomTempDisplay) roomTempDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      if (burnerTempDisplay && typeof data.burner_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.burner_temp)) burnerTempDisplay.textContent = data.burner_temp.toFixed(1) + '°C';
      else if (burnerTempDisplay) burnerTempDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      if (exhaustTempDisplay && typeof data.exhaust_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.exhaust_temp)) exhaustTempDisplay.textContent = data.exhaust_temp.toFixed(1) + '°C';
      else if (exhaustTempDisplay) exhaustTempDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      if (targetTemp && typeof data.target_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.target_temp)) targetTemp.textContent = data.target_temp.toFixed(0);
      else if (targetTemp) targetTemp.textContent = 'N/A';
      if (targetSlider && typeof data.target_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.target_temp)) targetSlider.value = data.target_temp;
      if (targetDisplay && typeof data.target_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.target_temp)) targetDisplay.textContent = data.target_temp.toFixed(0) + '°C';
      else if (targetDisplay) targetDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      const progress = (typeof data.water_temp === 'number' && typeof data.target_temp === 'number' && data.target_temp > 0) ? Math.min(100, (data.water_temp / data.target_temp) * 100) : 0;
      if (waterProgressBar) waterProgressBar.style.width = progress + '%';
      if (powerBtn) {
      if (data.power === "ON") {
      powerBtn.innerHTML = '<i class="fas fa-power-off"></i> WŁĄCZONY';
      powerBtn.classList.remove('power-off');
      powerBtn.classList.add('success');

      powerBtn.classList.remove('success');
      powerBtn.classList.add('power-off');
      }
      }
      if (flameIndicator && data.flame !== undefined) {
      flameIndicator.className = data.flame ? 'flame-indicator on' : 'flame-indicator off';
      }
      if (feederStatusIndicatorMini && data.feeder_active !== undefined && data.reverseFeederActive !== undefined) feederStatusIndicatorMini.className = 'status-indicator ' + (data.feeder_active || data.reverseFeederActive ? 'status-active' : 'status-inactive');

      if (feederStatus && cycleProgressBar && cycleTimer && data.currentPhaseDuration !== undefined && data.timeRemainingInPhase !== undefined) {
      let feederText = "PAUZA";
      let progressBarColor = 'var(--feeder-pause-color)';
      let totalPhaseDuration = data.currentPhaseDuration;
      let remainingTimeInPhase = data.timeRemainingInPhase;
      if (data.feederCycleState !== undefined) {
      switch (data.feederCycleState) {
      case 0: feederText = "PRZERWA"; progressBarColor = 'var(--feeder-pause-color)'; break;
      case 1: feederText = "PODAWANIE"; progressBarColor = 'var(--feeder-forward-color)'; break;
      case 2: feederText = "KRÓTKA PRZERWA"; progressBarColor = 'var(--feeder-pause-color)'; break;
      case 3: feederText = "COFANIE"; progressBarColor = 'var(--feeder-reverse-color)'; break;

      }
      feederStatus.innerHTML = `<span class="status-indicator ${(data.feeder_active || data.reverseFeederActive) ? 'status-active' : 'status-inactive'}"></span> PODAJNIK: ${feederText}`;

      feederStatus.classList.toggle('off', !(data.feeder_active || data.reverseFeederActive));
      const progressPercentage = totalPhaseDuration > 0 ? ((totalPhaseDuration - remainingTimeInPhase) / totalPhaseDuration) * 100 : 0;

      const currentBurnerHoursParts = burnerHoursDisplay.textContent.split(':');
      let currentBurnerMinutes = parseInt(currentBurnerHoursParts[0] || 0) * 60 + parseInt(currentBurnerHoursParts[1] || 0);
      // Prawdopodobnie to powinno zależeć od 'burner_active' lub 'flame' z ESP32, nie od 'power' button
      if (data.flame) { // Jeśli płomień jest aktywny
      currentBurnerMinutes += (1/60); // Zaktualizuj minuty, jeśli płomień jest aktywny
      }
      const newBurnerHours = Math.floor(currentBurnerMinutes / 60);
      const newBurnerMinutes = Math.floor(currentBurnerMinutes % 60);
      if (burnerHoursDisplay) burnerHoursDisplay.textContent = `${newBurnerHours.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:${newBurnerMinutes.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
      } else if (burnerHoursDisplay) {
      burnerHoursDisplay.textContent = 'N/A'; // Ustaw N/A, jeśli dane są niepoprawne
      }
      // --- Koniec problematycznego fragmentu ---
      calculateCost();
      const efficiency = (typeof data.water_temp === 'number' && !isNaN(data.water_temp)) ? Math.min(100, (data.water_temp / 85) * 100).toFixed(0) : 'N/A';
      if (efficiencyFill) efficiencyFill.style.width = `${efficiency}%`;
      if (efficiencyLabel) efficiencyLabel.textContent = `${efficiency}% Wydajność`;
      if (cleanCountdownDisplay && typeof data.time_to_clean === 'number' && !isNaN(data.time_to_clean)) {
      const cleanHours = Math.floor(data.time_to_clean / 3600);
      const cleanMinutes = Math.floor((data.time_to_clean % 3600) / 60);
      const cleanSeconds = Math.floor(data.time_to_clean % 60);
      cleanCountdownDisplay.textContent =
      `${cleanHours.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:${cleanMinutes.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:${cleanSeconds.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
      } else if (cleanCountdownDisplay) {
      cleanCountdownDisplay.textContent = 'N/A';
      }
      }
      // --- Wysyłanie komand do ESP32 (teraz przez MQTT) ---
      function sendCommand(cmd, value = null) {
      const payload = value !== null ? {command: cmd, value: value} : {command: cmd};
      if (client && client.connected) {
      publishMqttMessage(MQTT_TOPICS.control, JSON.stringify(payload));
      } else {
      appendMqttLog("OSTRZEŻENIE MQTT", "Nie połączono z brokerem MQTT, komenda nie wysłana!", 'error');
      console.error("MQTT client not connected, command not sent via MQTT.");
      }
      if (cmd === 'reset_history') {
      if (resetMessageDiv) {
      resetMessageDiv.textContent = 'Komenda resetowania danych wysłana. Odśwież stronę po chwili.';
      resetMessageDiv.style.color = 'var(--warning)';
      }
      } else if (cmd === 'reset_session_uptime') {
      console.log('Komenda resetowania czasu pracy sesji wysłana.');
      }
      }
      // --- Event Handlers ---
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => { // Cały kod JS jest teraz w DOMContentLoaded
      // Zapewnienie, że elementy istnieją przed dodaniem EventListener (dodano do wszystkich)
      const autoCleanToggle = document.getElementById('auto-clean-toggle');
      if (autoCleanToggle) {
      autoCleanToggle.addEventListener('change', () => {
      sendCommand('autoclean', autoCleanToggle.checked);
      });
      }
      if (mqttConnectBtn) mqttConnectBtn.addEventListener('click', connectMQTT);
      if (mqttDisconnectBtn) mqttDisconnectBtn.addEventListener('click', disconnectMQTT);
      if (powerBtn) {
      powerBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const currentStateText = powerBtn.textContent.trim();
      let newPowerState;
      if (currentStateText.includes("WŁĄCZONY")) {
      newPowerState = "OFF";
      } else {
      newPowerState = "ON";
      }
      publishMqttMessage(MQTT_TOPICS.power, newPowerState);
      });
      }
      if (targetSlider) {
      targetSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
      const value = parseInt(targetSlider.value);
      if (targetDisplay) targetDisplay.textContent = value + '°C';
      publishMqttMessage(MQTT_TOPICS.targetTemp, value.toString());
      });
      }
      if (ashBtn) {
      ashBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      sendCommand('clean');
      });
      }
      if (updateCleanBtn) {
      updateCleanBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const hours = parseInt(cleanHoursInput.value || 0);
      const minutes = parseInt(cleanMinutesInput.value || 0);
      const seconds = parseInt(cleanSecondsInput.value || 0);
      const totalSeconds = (hours * 3600) + (minutes * 60) + seconds;
      sendCommand('set_clean_time', totalSeconds);
      });
      }
      if (feedTimeInput && pauseTimeInput) {
      feedTimeInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const onTime = parseInt(feedTimeInput.value || 0);
      const offTime = parseInt(pauseTimeInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_feed_times', { on: onTime, off: offTime });
      });
      pauseTimeInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const onTime = parseInt(feedTimeInput.value || 0);
      const offTime = parseInt(pauseTimeInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_feed_times', { on: onTime, off: offTime });
      });
      }
      if (maintenanceFeedInput && maintenancePauseInput) {
      maintenanceFeedInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const maintenanceOnTime = parseInt(maintenanceFeedInput.value || 0);
      const maintenanceOffTime = parseInt(maintenancePauseInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_maintenance_feed_times', { on: maintenanceOnTime, off: maintenanceOffTime });
      });
      maintenancePauseInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const maintenanceOnTime = parseInt(maintenanceFeedInput.value || 0);
      const maintenanceOffTime = parseInt(maintenancePauseInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_maintenance_feed_times', { on: maintenanceOnTime, off: maintenanceOffTime });
      });
      }
      if (blowerManualToggle && blowerManualControlsDiv) {
      blowerManualToggle.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const isChecked = blowerManualToggle.checked;
      sendCommand('set_blower_manual', isChecked);
      blowerManualControlsDiv.style.display = isChecked ? 'block' : 'none';
      });
      }
      if (blowerWorkPowerSlider && blowerWorkPowerDisplay) {
      blowerWorkPowerSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerWorkPowerSlider.value);
      blowerWorkPowerDisplay.textContent = value + '%';
      });
      blowerWorkPowerSlider.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerWorkPowerSlider.value);
      sendCommand('set_blower_work_power', value);
      });
      }
      if (blowerPurgeManualPowerSlider && blowerPurgeManualPowerDisplay) {
      blowerPurgeManualPowerSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerPurgeManualPowerSlider.value);
      blowerPurgeManualPowerDisplay.textContent = value + '%';
      });
      blowerPurgeManualPowerSlider.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerPurgeManualPowerSlider.value);
      sendCommand('set_blower_purge_manual_power', value);
      });
      }
      if (blowerMaintenanceManualPowerSlider && blowerMaintenanceManualPowerDisplay) {
      blowerMaintenanceManualPowerSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerMaintenanceManualPowerSlider.value);
      blowerMaintenanceManualPowerDisplay.textContent = value + '%';
      });
      blowerMaintenanceManualPowerSlider.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const value = parseInt(blowerMaintenanceManualPowerSlider.value);
      sendCommand('set_blower_maintenance_manual_power', value);
      });
      }
      if (blowerPurgeToggle && blowerPurgeTimesContainer) {
      blowerPurgeToggle.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const isChecked = blowerPurgeToggle.checked;
      sendCommand('set_blower_purge_mode', isChecked);
      blowerPurgeTimesContainer.style.display = isChecked ? 'flex' : 'none';
      });
      }
      if (blowerPurgeOnInput && blowerPurgeOffInput) {
      blowerPurgeOnInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const onTime = parseInt(blowerPurgeOnInput.value || 0);
      const offTime = parseInt(blowerPurgeOffInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_blower_purge_times', { on: onTime, off: offTime });
      });
      blowerPurgeOffInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
      const onTime = parseInt(blowerPurgeOnInput.value || 0);
      const offTime = parseInt(blowerPurgeOffInput.value || 0);
      sendCommand('set_blower_purge_times', { on: onTime, off: offTime });
      });
      }
      if (resetHistoryBtn && resetPasswordInput) {
      resetHistoryBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const password = resetPasswordInput.value;
      sendCommand('reset_history', password);
      });
      }
      if (resetSessionUptimeBtn) {
      resetSessionUptimeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      sendCommand('reset_session_uptime');
      });
      }
      // Chart switching (for temperature chart's individual datasets)
      document.querySelectorAll('#temperature-chart-toggles .dataset-toggle').forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function() {
      const chartType = this.dataset.chart;
      const datasetIndex = chartDatasetMap[chartType];
      if (datasetIndex !== undefined && temperatureChartInstance) {
      const isHidden = temperatureChartInstance.isDatasetVisible(datasetIndex);
      temperatureChartInstance.setDatasetVisibility(datasetIndex, !isHidden);
      this.classList.toggle('active', !isHidden);
      temperatureChartInstance.update();
      }
      });
      });
      // Chart switching (for main chart types)
      document.querySelectorAll('#main-chart-switcher .chart-switch').forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function() {
      const chartType = this.dataset.chartType;
      document.querySelectorAll('#main-chart-switcher .chart-switch').forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
      this.classList.add('active');
      // Hide all chart containers (added checks for existence)
      if (chartContainerTemp) chartContainerTemp.style.display = 'none';
      if (chartContainerConsumption) chartContainerConsumption.style.display = 'none';
      if (chartContainerDailyConsumption) chartContainerDailyConsumption.style.display = 'none';
      if (chartContainerMonthlyConsumption) chartContainerMonthlyConsumption.style.display = 'none';
      if (chartContainerYearlyConsumption) chartContainerYearlyConsumption.style.display = 'none';
      if (chartContainerGlobalConsumption) chartContainerGlobalConsumption.style.display = 'none';
      // Hide/show temperature toggles (added check for existence)
      if (temperatureChartToggles) temperatureChartToggles.style.display = 'none';
      // Show the selected chart container and reset zoom for line charts
      switch (chartType) {
      case 'temperature':
      if (chartContainerTemp) chartContainerTemp.style.display = 'block';
      if (temperatureChartToggles) temperatureChartToggles.style.display = 'flex';
      if (temperatureChartInstance) {
      temperatureChartInstance.resetZoom();
      temperatureChartInstance.resize();
      }
      break;
      case 'consumption':
      if (chartContainerConsumption) chartContainerConsumption.style.display = 'block';
      if (consumptionChartInstance) {
      consumptionChartInstance.resetZoom();
      consumptionChartInstance.resize();
      }
      break;
      case 'daily-consumption':
      if (chartContainerDailyConsumption) chartContainerDailyConsumption.style.display = 'block';
      if (dailyConsumptionChartInstance) dailyConsumptionChartInstance.resize();
      break;
      case 'monthly-consumption':
      if (chartContainerMonthlyConsumption) chartContainerMonthlyConsumption.style.display = 'block';
      if (monthlyConsumptionChartInstance) monthlyConsumptionChartInstance.resize();
      break;
      case 'yearly-consumption':
      if (chartContainerYearlyConsumption) chartContainerYearlyConsumption.style.display = 'block';
      if (yearlyConsumptionChartInstance) yearlyConsumptionChartInstance.resize();
      break;
      case 'global-consumption':
      if (chartContainerGlobalConsumption) chartContainerGlobalConsumption.style.display = 'block';
      if (globalConsumptionChartInstance) globalConsumptionChartInstance.resize();
      break;
      }
      });
      });
      // Chart zoom controls (for temperature chart)
      const zoomInTempBtn = document.getElementById('zoom-in');
      const zoomOutTempBtn = document.getElementById('zoom-out');
      const zoomResetTempBtn = document.getElementById('zoom-reset');
      if (zoomInTempBtn) zoomInTempBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (temperatureChartInstance) temperatureChartInstance.zoom(1.1); });
      if (zoomOutTempBtn) zoomOutTempBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (temperatureChartInstance) temperatureChartInstance.zoom(0.9); });
      if (zoomResetTempBtn) zoomResetTempBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (temperatureChartInstance) temperatureChartInstance.resetZoom(); });
      // Zoom controls for consumption chart
      const zoomInConsBtn = document.getElementById('consumption-zoom-in');
      const zoomOutConsBtn = document.getElementById('consumption-zoom-out');
      const zoomResetConsBtn = document.getElementById('consumption-zoom-reset');
      if (zoomInConsBtn) zoomInConsBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (consumptionChartInstance) consumptionChartInstance.zoom(1.1); });
      if (zoomOutConsBtn) zoomOutConsBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (consumptionChartInstance) consumptionChartInstance.zoom(0.9); });
      if (zoomResetConsBtn) zoomResetConsBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if (consumptionChartInstance) consumptionChartInstance.resetZoom(); });
      // History range buttons (placeholder for future implementation)
      historyRangeButtons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function() {
      historyRangeButtons.forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
      this.classList.add('active');
      const range = this.dataset.range;
      console.log(`Selected history range: ${range}`);
      });
      });
      // Cost calculation logic
      function calculateCost() {
      const price = parseFloat(pelletPriceInput.value || 0);
      const actualConsumptionRate = parseFloat(pelletAmount.textContent || 0);
      const burnerHoursParts = (burnerHoursDisplay && burnerHoursDisplay.textContent) ? burnerHoursDisplay.textContent.split(':') : ['00', '00'];
      const burnerHoursTotal = parseInt(burnerHoursParts[0] || 0) * 60 + parseInt(burnerHoursParts[1] || 0);
      if (!isNaN(price) && !isNaN(actualConsumptionRate) && !isNaN(burnerHoursTotal)) {
      const estimatedCost = price * actualConsumptionRate * burnerHoursTotal / 60; // Dziel przez 60, bo burnerHoursTotal jest w minutach
      if (estimatedCostDisplay) estimatedCostDisplay.textContent = `${estimatedCost.toFixed(2)} PLN`;
      if (totalCalculatedCost) totalCalculatedCost.textContent = `${estimatedCost.toFixed(2)} PLN`;
      } else {
      if (estimatedCostDisplay) estimatedCostDisplay.textContent = `N/A`;
      if (totalCalculatedCost) totalCalculatedCost.textContent = `N/A`;
      }
      }
      if (pelletPriceInput) pelletPriceInput.addEventListener('input', calculateCost);
      // Initial state fetch and MQTT connection
      // AUTOMATYCZNE POŁĄCZENIE MQTT PO ZAŁADOWANIU STRONY (dla połączenia internetowego)
      connectMQTT();
      });
      </script>
      </body>
